Interface TestSubject

All Known Implementing Classes:
ChatBotGeneratorTest, ChatBotPlatformTest, ChatBotSimulationTest, ChatBotSimulationTest, ChatBotTest, TestRunner
public interface TestSubject
The TestSubject interface defines the methods for a subject that can notify an observer about changes or updates, specifically in the context of test results.

Any class that implements this interface can attach or detach a TestResultObserver and signal updates (such as test marks and feedback) to the attached observer.

  • Method Details

    • signal

      void signal(int marks, String feedback)
      Signals test results (marks and feedback) to the attached observer.

      This method is used to send test results to the observer, which will then handle the updates as required.

      Parameters:
      marks - the marks obtained for the test.
      feedback - the feedback provided for the test.

    • attach

      void attach(TestResultObserver t)
      Attaches a TestResultObserver to this subject.

      This method allows an observer to receive updates about test results.

      Parameters:
      t - the TestResultObserver to be attached.

    • detach

      void detach(TestResultObserver t)
      Detaches the currently attached TestResultObserver from this subject.

      This method ensures that the observer will no longer receive updates about test results.

      Parameters:
      t - the TestResultObserver to be detached.
